1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,433
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:02,733
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,812 --> 00:00:04,812
(Episode 57)

4
00:00:04,812 --> 00:00:06,012
What delivery? What kind of delivery?

5
00:00:06,500 --> 00:00:08,240
- The DNA test results.
- What?

6
00:00:09,257 --> 00:00:10,324
Open it. Hurry.

7
00:00:10,324 --> 00:00:11,324
Hurry.

8
00:00:11,587 --> 00:00:12,587
Quick.

9
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:25,900
(Lee Yeong Hwa and Kang Yeon Ja
are biologically related.)

10
00:00:28,593 --> 00:00:29,593
What?

11
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:34,700
(Lee Yeong Hwa and Kang Yeon Ja
are biologically related.)

12
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:39,700
What is this?

13
00:00:40,628 --> 00:00:42,828
They really were mother and daughter?

14
00:00:46,384 --> 00:00:48,640
No way.

15
00:00:49,205 --> 00:00:50,843
Then if this comes out,

16
00:00:51,391 --> 00:00:52,797
what will happen to us, honey?

17
00:00:53,104 --> 00:00:54,632
What do you mean, what will happen?

18
00:00:54,632 --> 00:00:55,632
Split four ways.

19
00:00:56,374 --> 00:00:58,074
- My nose is done for.
- What?

20
00:00:58,785 --> 00:01:00,729
She'll be my sister,

21
00:01:00,729 --> 00:01:03,400
and your sister-in-law
you never asked for.

22
00:01:04,086 --> 00:01:06,553
Kang Yeon Ja,
the invincible sister-in-law.

23
00:01:06,769 --> 00:01:09,136
What? That woman is my sister-in-law?

24
00:01:10,883 --> 00:01:14,584
You're right. Why didn't I think of that?

25
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:18,139
Come to think of it,
Mother said she'd been...

26
00:01:18,139 --> 00:01:20,139
to Gyeol's landlord's house, didn't she?

27
00:01:20,501 --> 00:01:21,552
I'm going crazy here.

28
00:01:21,963 --> 00:01:24,317
How is everything around us a landmine?

29
00:01:25,416 --> 00:01:26,483
You're right.

30
00:01:27,072 --> 00:01:29,539
That day, Mother brought a lot of stuff...

31
00:01:29,539 --> 00:01:30,739
to Kang Yeon Ja's house.

32
00:01:31,218 --> 00:01:34,960
And she still kept her mouth shut with us?

33
00:01:35,152 --> 00:01:38,003
My goodness. This is ridiculous.

34
00:01:40,426 --> 00:01:41,493
- Crystal.
- Yeah?

35
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,800
- Look at me.
- Okay.

36
00:01:43,025 --> 00:01:46,213
- Poker face again.
- Okay.

37
00:01:47,168 --> 00:01:48,301
- Poker face.
- Poker face.

38
00:01:48,868 --> 00:01:49,868
- Poker face.
- Poker face.

39
00:01:49,868 --> 00:01:52,101
- Poker face.
- Poker face.

40
00:01:52,101 --> 00:01:53,101
- Poker face.
- Poker face.

41
00:01:53,623 --> 00:01:55,123
- Poker face.
- Poker face.

42
00:01:55,123 --> 00:01:57,981
Good grief. Have you no shame?

43
00:01:58,533 --> 00:02:01,256
What are you two doing in broad daylight
in front of the gate?

44
00:02:04,004 --> 00:02:05,160
What are you hiding there?

45
00:02:05,693 --> 00:02:06,877
Hiding what?

46
00:02:07,168 --> 00:02:09,601
I'm not hiding anything!

47
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,221
Seriously, how can you never tell...

48
00:02:11,221 --> 00:02:12,888
when to butt in and when not to?

49
00:02:14,921 --> 00:02:15,921
Let's go inside, Crystal.

50
00:02:19,636 --> 00:02:20,636
That guy, seriously.

51
00:02:22,237 --> 00:02:24,229
What is that document?

52
00:02:24,988 --> 00:02:27,317
I can't shake this bad feeling.

53
00:02:35,674 --> 00:02:36,674
Hello.

54
00:02:36,876 --> 00:02:38,869
Yes.

55
00:02:40,193 --> 00:02:42,683
Father, we're back.

56
00:02:42,849 --> 00:02:45,261
- Yes, we're back.
- You're home earlier than I expected.

57
00:02:46,352 --> 00:02:47,352
Yes.

58
00:02:48,152 --> 00:02:49,507
Hey, what's going on?

59
00:02:50,077 --> 00:02:52,344
Didn't you say you were going biking
with Intern Cho?

60
00:02:52,344 --> 00:02:55,077
Yes. But Grandpa called for me,
so I came back.

61
00:02:56,216 --> 00:02:58,613
I'm sorry I didn't tell you sooner...

62
00:02:59,090 --> 00:03:00,533
where I'd moved out to.

63
00:03:00,989 --> 00:03:02,355
Yeah, that wasn't great.

64
00:03:02,752 --> 00:03:05,523
That's something
you should've told your parents first.

65
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:12,528
- Honey.
- Honey.

66
00:03:12,727 --> 00:03:14,664
Why do I feel like this? I'm so dizzy.

67
00:03:15,201 --> 00:03:17,501
What's wrong? Are you feeling sick?

68
00:03:17,501 --> 00:03:19,291
My anemia is acting up.

69
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:21,133
Mother, I'll go inside.

70
00:03:21,491 --> 00:03:23,000
Yeah, let's go inside.

71
00:03:27,901 --> 00:03:29,257
Have a seat, Eun Ae.

72
00:03:29,257 --> 00:03:30,368
Okay.

73
00:03:32,597 --> 00:03:35,112
I heard from Gyeol that you installed...

74
00:03:35,299 --> 00:03:37,432
a people-finder app on Yeong Hwa's phone.

75
00:03:38,412 --> 00:03:39,412
Thank you.

76
00:03:39,852 --> 00:03:42,528
It's nothing. I didn't really do much.

77
00:03:43,131 --> 00:03:46,648
As for the senior date course we tried,

78
00:03:48,092 --> 00:03:49,859
I'm 100 percent satisfied.

79
00:03:51,137 --> 00:03:52,137
Really?

80
00:03:52,309 --> 00:03:55,455
Was there anything inconvenient
or was the route too complicated?

81
00:03:55,455 --> 00:03:57,955
No, it was planned very well.

82
00:03:58,273 --> 00:04:02,140
More than anything,
I liked the choice of locations.

83
00:04:02,857 --> 00:04:05,432
You included places that are popular...

84
00:04:05,715 --> 00:04:07,232
with young people too.

85
00:04:07,885 --> 00:04:11,152
It let us relive our youth...

86
00:04:11,853 --> 00:04:15,786
and also experience current trends.

87
00:04:16,615 --> 00:04:19,280
There's something people misunderstand.

88
00:04:19,815 --> 00:04:22,915
They think getting older
means your heart grows old too.

89
00:04:24,248 --> 00:04:27,936
But our hearts are always young.

90
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:30,160
I'm glad you liked it.

91
00:04:30,814 --> 00:04:34,381
I was worried it might feel unfamiliar
since you'd never been there before.

92
00:04:35,034 --> 00:04:37,201
We'll make good use of your feedback...

93
00:04:37,475 --> 00:04:39,864
and create even more diverse courses.

94
00:04:40,048 --> 00:04:42,469
Good. I'm looking forward to it.

95
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:47,949
You haven't had lunch, right?
We called you over at an awkward hour.

96
00:04:48,620 --> 00:04:52,005
Just wait a bit.
I'll prepare lunch quickly.

97
00:04:52,117 --> 00:04:54,017
You two haven't had lunch yet?

98
00:04:54,490 --> 00:04:55,490
What?

99
00:04:55,896 --> 00:04:59,496
We always eat at the same time,
like clockwork.

100
00:04:59,496 --> 00:05:00,765
We already ate.

101
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:04,021
Thank you, Grandma,

102
00:05:04,021 --> 00:05:05,533
but we'll just eat out.

103
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,144
You've already eaten.
Don't go to any trouble for us.

104
00:05:08,144 --> 00:05:11,728
No.
You installed something I needed most...

105
00:05:12,032 --> 00:05:14,893
and came all the way here
because Grandpa asked.

106
00:05:16,724 --> 00:05:18,591
While I prepare the meal,

107
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,456
why don't you go look around
Gyeol's room upstairs?

108
00:05:22,167 --> 00:05:23,840
Yeah, do that.

109
00:05:24,433 --> 00:05:27,781
This is usually my nap time.

110
00:05:28,624 --> 00:05:29,885
Go upstairs and chat.

111
00:05:30,651 --> 00:05:31,651
Get some rest, Grandpa.

112
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:36,621
Want to go upstairs for a bit?

113
00:05:41,316 --> 00:05:42,316
Seriously.

114
00:05:42,645 --> 00:05:44,539
Why? What's wrong?

115
00:05:45,767 --> 00:05:48,792
When Mother and that woman
came out of the room just now,

116
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,285
I almost fainted.

117
00:05:50,772 --> 00:05:53,639
They look exactly alike.

118
00:05:54,236 --> 00:05:55,931
Genes really are terrifying.

119
00:05:56,268 --> 00:05:59,333
I don't really see it with Kang Yeon Ja,
but...

120
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:02,512
They say genes often skip a generation.

121
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:05,751
This is getting ridiculous.

122
00:06:05,751 --> 00:06:07,951
Now even the granddaughter
is at our house?

123
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:11,445
Tell Gyeol to move back home right now.

124
00:06:11,727 --> 00:06:12,727
If he stays in that house,

125
00:06:13,021 --> 00:06:15,365
Mother will keep dropping by with food,

126
00:06:15,365 --> 00:06:17,532
and it'll only be a matter of time
before they recognize each other.

127
00:06:18,109 --> 00:06:19,809
Split those two up immediately too.

128
00:06:20,612 --> 00:06:22,968
Do you think Gyeol
would actually listen to me?

129
00:06:23,361 --> 00:06:24,528
What can I even do?

130
00:06:25,015 --> 00:06:27,368
Then what are we supposed to do?

131
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,700
I can't live like this.

132
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:31,833
I really can't. I just can't.

133
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,240
Food's ready. Where are you going?

134
00:06:38,717 --> 00:06:40,859
I'm not eating. I have somewhere to be.

135
00:06:41,341 --> 00:06:42,374
Going to work again?

136
00:06:42,980 --> 00:06:46,088
How is it that you never rest,
even on holidays?

137
00:06:46,204 --> 00:06:47,204
I'm heading out.

138
00:06:47,652 --> 00:06:48,652
Seung Ri.

139
00:06:49,782 --> 00:06:52,755
I know I've been interfering
in your life lately...

140
00:06:52,755 --> 00:06:54,920
and saying things you don't want to hear.

141
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:59,096
But please do as your mother says, okay?

142
00:06:59,539 --> 00:07:01,101
I've lived long enough to know.

143
00:07:01,321 --> 00:07:03,283
When it comes to men...

144
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:12,464
My smart, kind daughter never caused me
a moment of worry growing up.

145
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:15,925
How did she end up like that?

146
00:07:21,826 --> 00:07:22,826
What's going on?

147
00:07:23,501 --> 00:07:24,601
What do you think?

148
00:07:24,991 --> 00:07:26,791
The maid of this house
is telling you to come eat.

149
00:07:27,147 --> 00:07:29,709
Honestly, why even say things like that?

150
00:07:29,831 --> 00:07:31,231
Why would you call yourself a maid?

151
00:07:31,568 --> 00:07:33,400
If you don't want me thinking that,

152
00:07:33,729 --> 00:07:35,637
then let me see those documents
you're looking at too.

153
00:07:36,433 --> 00:07:37,433
What?

154
00:07:40,232 --> 00:07:42,597
I know all about Madam's search
for her daughter.

155
00:07:42,779 --> 00:07:45,221
Why are you keeping it so secret from me?

156
00:07:45,701 --> 00:07:47,272
Is there something
I'm not supposed to know?

157
00:07:47,272 --> 00:07:48,925
Of course not.

158
00:07:49,283 --> 00:07:50,675
I'll finish up and come out.

159
00:07:52,015 --> 00:07:53,015
Hurry up.

160
00:08:05,223 --> 00:08:08,423
Call Seung Wu.
We might as well eat together.

161
00:08:08,824 --> 00:08:10,324
He'll come home when he's ready.

162
00:08:32,047 --> 00:08:33,899
How is his skin even better than mine?

163
00:08:39,344 --> 00:08:40,672
And his eyelashes are just...

164
00:08:48,235 --> 00:08:50,605
Are you okay? Sorry.

165
00:08:52,393 --> 00:08:55,789
But why were you staring at my face
like that?

166
00:08:55,904 --> 00:08:57,971
Why would I stare at your face?

167
00:08:58,087 --> 00:09:00,120
I was just trying to wake you up
and tell you to leave.

168
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,100
Do you even know what time it is?

169
00:09:03,712 --> 00:09:05,544
What time is it?

170
00:09:06,816 --> 00:09:08,808
Why didn't you wake me up?

171
00:09:08,808 --> 00:09:10,736
It's been four and a half hours.

172
00:09:10,942 --> 00:09:13,680
Wait. Then how much is the penalty?

173
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,931
It's 30 dollars an hour, so...

174
00:09:16,636 --> 00:09:17,792
It's 155 dollars.

175
00:09:19,188 --> 00:09:21,603
This is bad. Really bad.

176
00:09:22,933 --> 00:09:25,323
Can I pay in installments?

177
00:09:25,323 --> 00:09:27,640
Money's really tight for me these days.

178
00:09:27,640 --> 00:09:28,640
Forget it.

179
00:09:29,412 --> 00:09:32,165
More importantly,
I think we should revise the rules.

180
00:09:32,475 --> 00:09:33,720
Let's get rid of rule number one.

181
00:09:34,976 --> 00:09:36,973
Let's get rid
of the day-me-night-you rule.

182
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:40,805
What? You mean
stop separating daytime and nighttime...

183
00:09:40,805 --> 00:09:42,528
and use the studio freely?

184
00:09:42,528 --> 00:09:45,060
Yes. As a former medical student,

185
00:09:45,060 --> 00:09:47,408
looking at it from a medical perspective,

186
00:09:47,872 --> 00:09:50,339
it seems like a very unfair rule for you.

187
00:09:51,040 --> 00:09:54,381
When your body clock gets reversed,
it disrupts your hormones,

188
00:09:54,381 --> 00:09:57,800
weakens your immune system,
and significantly reduces concentration.

189
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,400
Thank you, Ms. Cho.

190
00:10:00,254 --> 00:10:03,568
Bless you for being so considerate.

191
00:10:04,050 --> 00:10:05,217
You always go around blessing people.

192
00:10:07,798 --> 00:10:09,565
I forgot. I need to feed my babies.

193
00:10:15,779 --> 00:10:17,932
Were you hungry, Bung Nim?

194
00:10:17,932 --> 00:10:20,200
Wait a second. What did you just say?

195
00:10:22,315 --> 00:10:23,915
What did you say the goldfish's name was?

196
00:10:24,485 --> 00:10:25,864
Bung Nim. Why?

197
00:10:26,247 --> 00:10:29,205
Bung Nim and Eun Nim...
Don't tell me that's me?

198
00:10:29,653 --> 00:10:32,037
What? Of course not.

199
00:10:32,260 --> 00:10:35,093
As if this cute goldfish
is supposed to be you.

200
00:10:35,971 --> 00:10:37,352
Right, Bung Nim?

201
00:10:37,547 --> 00:10:41,447
Isn't that an insult? A humiliation?

202
00:10:42,075 --> 00:10:43,108
You're cute.

203
00:10:47,436 --> 00:10:51,421
Earlier in the yard, when you asked
what I thought of Team Manager Ko,

204
00:10:51,891 --> 00:10:54,040
did you already know
those two were dating?

205
00:10:54,964 --> 00:10:57,285
I had a feeling they liked each other,

206
00:10:57,501 --> 00:11:00,992
but since neither of them said
anything themselves, I just kept watching.

207
00:11:01,828 --> 00:11:03,821
Then last night, Team Manager Ko told me.

208
00:11:04,275 --> 00:11:07,755
Last night? When you saw him at the gate?

209
00:11:10,199 --> 00:11:13,112
What do you think of him
as Eun Ae's boyfriend?

210
00:11:13,873 --> 00:11:15,947
I can't fault him as a person,

211
00:11:17,308 --> 00:11:19,077
but when I think about his parents...

212
00:11:19,693 --> 00:11:21,237
What was that all about earlier?

213
00:11:21,718 --> 00:11:23,520
Showing up out of nowhere with beef,

214
00:11:24,039 --> 00:11:25,809
talking about how
we're practically family,

215
00:11:25,809 --> 00:11:28,563
then grilling me about my real birthday
before rushing off.

216
00:11:29,290 --> 00:11:30,880
None of that really matters.

217
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:33,187
The people involved
are Eun Ae and Team Manager Ko.

218
00:11:33,908 --> 00:11:36,808
You're not going to oppose them dating,
are you?

219
00:11:37,211 --> 00:11:40,379
It's the first real relationship
our daughter has had in her 30s.

220
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:42,507
Why would I oppose it?

221
00:11:43,485 --> 00:11:46,923
I'm just going to pretend I don't know
until she tells me herself.

222
00:11:48,469 --> 00:11:50,741
You always told me to stop meddling
in the kids' lives.

223
00:11:51,434 --> 00:11:53,301
Good thinking.

224
00:11:55,173 --> 00:11:58,861
By the way,
I wonder if Bit Na's having fun.

225
00:12:01,784 --> 00:12:04,024
Did you prepare all this by yourself?

226
00:12:04,254 --> 00:12:07,035
Yeah. I wanted Bit Na and you to enjoy it,

227
00:12:07,433 --> 00:12:08,700
so I put in a lot of effort since dawn.

228
00:12:09,140 --> 00:12:10,637
It's really good, Auntie.

229
00:12:11,282 --> 00:12:12,282
Thank you.

230
00:12:12,993 --> 00:12:13,993
Aren't you going to try it, Eun Hyeong?

231
00:12:14,583 --> 00:12:17,029
This is a new menu item I developed.
Want to try it?

232
00:12:17,304 --> 00:12:18,304
Sure.

233
00:12:23,298 --> 00:12:26,098
There's a strangely harmonious blend
of flavors.

234
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:30,920
How should I put it? It's like
a collaboration between East and West,

235
00:12:30,920 --> 00:12:32,275
fresh and creative.

236
00:12:32,275 --> 00:12:33,275
Wait.

237
00:12:35,844 --> 00:12:37,044
Hey, this is good.

238
00:12:37,531 --> 00:12:38,564
- Really?
- Yeah.

239
00:12:39,153 --> 00:12:42,453
You're the first person
who's ever complimented my bindaetteok.

240
00:12:42,610 --> 00:12:45,221
Really? No way.
This totally tastes like a hit.

241
00:12:45,553 --> 00:12:46,553
- Right?
- Yeah.

242
00:12:46,553 --> 00:12:48,353
You sure know what's good.

243
00:12:50,409 --> 00:12:53,809
Anyway, how have you not changed at all?

244
00:12:54,987 --> 00:12:56,720
You look exactly the same
as you did in high school.

245
00:12:57,460 --> 00:12:58,460
You really have a baby face.

246
00:12:59,359 --> 00:13:00,851
Me? A baby face?

247
00:13:02,477 --> 00:13:04,944
That's the first time
I've ever heard that.

248
00:13:08,334 --> 00:13:09,801
Dad, what's a baby face?

249
00:13:10,955 --> 00:13:12,255
A baby face.

250
00:13:12,255 --> 00:13:14,112
Literally, "child face."

251
00:13:14,584 --> 00:13:17,056
It means someone looks younger
than their actual age.

252
00:13:17,585 --> 00:13:19,085
Bit Na, do you agree?

253
00:13:27,295 --> 00:13:30,832
Dad, if you're done eating,
should we go play with bubbles now?

254
00:13:31,741 --> 00:13:34,171
As expected.
Silence is the most reliable truth.

255
00:13:34,672 --> 00:13:36,331
Okay. Let's go play with bubbles.

256
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,683
Auntie, come after you're done eating too.

257
00:13:44,183 --> 00:13:45,216
Bit Na, come here.

258
00:13:56,149 --> 00:13:59,472
We can't have you getting hurt, Bit Na.

259
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:04,901
Bit Na, I want to join.

260
00:14:04,901 --> 00:14:06,201
- Let me do it too.
- Come here.

261
00:14:06,525 --> 00:14:07,525
Hurry up.

262
00:14:07,525 --> 00:14:08,525
Look at this.

263
00:14:12,276 --> 00:14:13,888
- This is really fun.
- Right?

264
00:14:13,888 --> 00:14:14,988
I figured it out now. Look.

265
00:14:16,034 --> 00:14:17,634
You're really good at this!

266
00:14:19,947 --> 00:14:22,761
I seriously don't understand...

267
00:14:22,761 --> 00:14:25,667
why you moved out
when you had such a big, nice room.

268
00:14:26,141 --> 00:14:29,005
You keep losing to Eun Hyeong
and end up on the floor every night.

269
00:14:30,024 --> 00:14:31,941
Do you know how excited I get every day?

270
00:14:31,941 --> 00:14:34,787
My heart starts racing
and my competitive spirit kicks in.

271
00:14:37,509 --> 00:14:40,409
I want to see photos of you
when you were little, Team Manager.

272
00:14:41,601 --> 00:14:43,912
The Team Manager I met when I was five...

273
00:14:43,912 --> 00:14:45,479
must still be there in those pictures.

274
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:47,733
Pictures?

275
00:14:48,277 --> 00:14:51,347
Well, I don't really have many photos
from when I was little.

276
00:14:51,809 --> 00:14:55,609
Even so, don't you have
a childhood photo album?

277
00:14:56,605 --> 00:14:58,029
I'll show you sometime.

278
00:14:58,225 --> 00:15:00,587
I don't even know where it's stored.

279
00:15:01,269 --> 00:15:02,325
Okay.

280
00:15:03,423 --> 00:15:05,156
But I felt this again today.

281
00:15:05,479 --> 00:15:08,279
Why did things become strained
between you and your parents?

282
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:12,304
The truth is, Eun Ae...

283
00:15:16,464 --> 00:15:18,781
I'll tell you about that later.

284
00:15:19,356 --> 00:15:20,523
A little later.

285
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:24,160
Okay.
Just tell me whenever you're comfortable.

286
00:15:25,064 --> 00:15:26,344
Just remember one thing.

287
00:15:26,901 --> 00:15:29,573
I won't hide things from you,

288
00:15:29,713 --> 00:15:31,061
or lie to you.

289
00:15:31,483 --> 00:15:34,397
I just need a little more time...

290
00:15:34,902 --> 00:15:36,272
before I can tell you everything.

291
00:15:37,452 --> 00:15:39,784
Of course. I'm good at waiting.

292
00:15:40,149 --> 00:15:42,075
I'll wait for anything related to you,
Team Manager.

293
00:15:44,125 --> 00:15:45,733
Have you been well?

294
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:46,992
Of course.

295
00:15:47,740 --> 00:15:49,547
Did you come to see Min Ho?

296
00:15:49,547 --> 00:15:52,347
No.
I came to see the Chairman and you, Madam.

297
00:15:52,933 --> 00:15:54,629
These are workout clothes for you two.

298
00:15:54,813 --> 00:15:56,272
For when you go out on walks.

299
00:15:57,148 --> 00:15:58,867
You didn't have to bring this.

300
00:15:59,689 --> 00:16:01,222
The Chairman is sleeping right now.

301
00:16:02,034 --> 00:16:04,381
I'll greet him before I leave
once he wakes up.

302
00:16:04,601 --> 00:16:05,701
Have you had lunch?

303
00:16:06,414 --> 00:16:07,414
Not yet.

304
00:16:07,744 --> 00:16:09,792
Really? Perfect.

305
00:16:10,180 --> 00:16:13,447
Gyeol happened to come by,
and I'm almost done preparing lunch.

306
00:16:14,769 --> 00:16:17,636
Just wait here a little while.
I'll call you when it's ready.

307
00:16:27,726 --> 00:16:29,088
I can't believe it.

308
00:16:29,541 --> 00:16:33,241
That little girl from the playground
is sitting in my room right now.

309
00:16:36,243 --> 00:16:39,533
What? Why are you looking at me like that?

310
00:16:39,893 --> 00:16:40,960
You're making my heart race.

311
00:16:41,753 --> 00:16:43,291
Really?

312
00:16:48,137 --> 00:16:49,440
Let's get out of here.

313
00:16:49,824 --> 00:16:51,241
Even if the maid is here to help,

314
00:16:51,241 --> 00:16:52,941
I should at least go set out the utensils.

315
00:16:54,583 --> 00:16:56,183
You were just saying
your heart was racing.

316
00:17:01,069 --> 00:17:02,069
There.

317
00:17:02,385 --> 00:17:03,418
Come on.

318
00:17:04,533 --> 00:17:05,717
That's not fair.

319
00:17:19,829 --> 00:17:23,157
Seung Ri, what brings you here?
Don't tell me you're here to see me.

320
00:17:26,141 --> 00:17:27,941
What's wrong? Are you sick?

321
00:17:30,248 --> 00:17:31,507
Ko Gyeol, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

322
00:17:32,112 --> 00:17:33,747
What's going on? Why are you two...

323
00:17:36,353 --> 00:17:39,117
Hello, Chief, Manager Seo.

324
00:17:39,775 --> 00:17:42,357
We're only here
because Grandpa called us about work.

325
00:17:42,638 --> 00:17:43,638
Grandpa did?

326
00:17:44,472 --> 00:17:47,267
What? During the competition,

327
00:17:47,469 --> 00:17:48,969
he called you here about work?

328
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,555
Did you use the Grandpa card?

329
00:17:51,893 --> 00:17:54,184
Do you really think Grandpa
would do something that unfair?

330
00:17:54,531 --> 00:17:56,331
- Min Ho, you're here too.
- Yes.

331
00:17:56,604 --> 00:17:58,736
Everyone, come in. The food's ready.

332
00:17:59,007 --> 00:18:02,213
Grandma, I'm sorry I couldn't help.

333
00:18:02,386 --> 00:18:03,888
Let me set the table at least.

334
00:18:03,888 --> 00:18:06,123
It's all done. Don't worry about it.

335
00:18:06,522 --> 00:18:08,589
Madam, I should get going.

336
00:18:08,806 --> 00:18:10,459
I forgot I had another appointment.

337
00:18:10,657 --> 00:18:12,557
I'll greet the Chairman next time.

338
00:18:13,649 --> 00:18:15,285
Seung Ri. Seo Seung Ri!

339
00:18:15,973 --> 00:18:16,973
Ko Min Ho.

340
00:18:17,707 --> 00:18:18,896
Come into my room.

341
00:18:21,277 --> 00:18:23,512
Sorry? Yes.

342
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,451
You two should come eat.

343
00:18:28,985 --> 00:18:29,985
Okay.

344
00:18:30,899 --> 00:18:31,999
Let's go.

345
00:18:36,184 --> 00:18:38,824
They really picked a day for it.

346
00:18:39,372 --> 00:18:41,779
Min Ho and Seung Ri
both showed up all at once.

347
00:18:42,439 --> 00:18:43,896
What? Seung Ri's here?

348
00:18:44,721 --> 00:18:46,131
That little brat, seriously.

349
00:18:46,753 --> 00:18:47,843
Calm down.

350
00:18:49,516 --> 00:18:51,704
Is that really
what we should be worried about right now?

351
00:18:51,704 --> 00:18:53,488
We need to come up with a plan.

352
00:18:53,488 --> 00:18:54,788
What are we going to do?

353
00:18:55,812 --> 00:18:56,812
Right.

354
00:18:57,944 --> 00:19:01,928
Honey, I'm really hungry right now.

355
00:19:05,512 --> 00:19:08,003
Can't we eat first
and then come up with a plan?

356
00:19:08,299 --> 00:19:10,000
Crystal, right now,

357
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:13,200
the grandmother and granddaughter
are together outside.

358
00:19:13,665 --> 00:19:17,568
Do you think you can keep a poker face
if you go out there?

359
00:19:17,915 --> 00:19:20,189
No, absolutely not.

360
00:19:22,558 --> 00:19:25,387
Then for now,

361
00:19:25,584 --> 00:19:27,451
fill your stomach with water.

362
00:19:34,512 --> 00:19:38,589
No matter how desperate you were
about Seung Ri,

363
00:19:39,116 --> 00:19:40,635
proposing without her consent,

364
00:19:41,353 --> 00:19:44,504
and in a public place, no less?

365
00:19:45,875 --> 00:19:47,339
Did you not think
about how Seung Ri would feel?

366
00:19:48,336 --> 00:19:49,643
I have no excuse,

367
00:19:49,979 --> 00:19:52,320
but I had no choice at the time.

368
00:19:52,459 --> 00:19:53,931
Whatever the reason,

369
00:19:54,821 --> 00:19:57,480
do you remember what I said
during the first competition?

370
00:19:58,780 --> 00:20:00,891
I said
that my position is not one to inherit,

371
00:20:01,461 --> 00:20:03,128
but one to take responsibility for.

372
00:20:04,792 --> 00:20:08,952
I don't know who will become
the new leader of Kangsu Group,

373
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:13,451
but you're one of the people
who must take responsibility as well.

374
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:16,639
If you act so recklessly...

375
00:20:17,619 --> 00:20:20,587
in the company lobby of all places,
how can you lead the company?

376
00:20:21,937 --> 00:20:22,937
I'm sorry.

377
00:20:23,318 --> 00:20:26,385
As I've watched the competition unfold,

378
00:20:27,244 --> 00:20:30,432
I've been very pleased to see
how hard you've worked...

379
00:20:31,793 --> 00:20:33,060
to keep the race fair.

380
00:20:33,835 --> 00:20:36,115
The race within the company is important,

381
00:20:36,797 --> 00:20:40,379
but never forget that life itself...

382
00:20:41,308 --> 00:20:42,308
is a much bigger race.

383
00:20:42,591 --> 00:20:44,891
Yes, Grandpa. I'll remember that.

384
00:20:48,020 --> 00:20:50,069
- Are you working?
- Yes, Mom.

385
00:20:52,036 --> 00:20:55,776
Why'd you suddenly go to
the Chairman's house after your bike ride?

386
00:20:57,157 --> 00:21:01,257
The Chairman and Grandma
tried out the Joy program,

387
00:21:01,462 --> 00:21:03,269
and they called us over
to give their feedback.

388
00:21:03,899 --> 00:21:05,328
Is that really all?

389
00:21:05,841 --> 00:21:08,371
What do you mean?
What else would there be?

390
00:21:09,291 --> 00:21:11,451
Mom, I have something to tell you.

391
00:21:12,531 --> 00:21:15,901
You said Team Manager's grandmother
is looking for someone.

392
00:21:16,100 --> 00:21:17,133
Yeah.

393
00:21:17,133 --> 00:21:19,933
I've been developing a people-finder app,

394
00:21:20,261 --> 00:21:22,661
and I installed it on her phone today.

395
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:24,500
Really? Good job.

396
00:21:25,171 --> 00:21:27,472
Mom, so what I was thinking is,

397
00:21:28,555 --> 00:21:29,741
maybe you could...

398
00:21:29,741 --> 00:21:30,741
Cho Eun Ae.

399
00:21:31,600 --> 00:21:34,715
I know what you're about to say,
but I have no one I'm looking for.

400
00:21:38,523 --> 00:21:40,000
What should I do, Joy?

401
00:21:40,520 --> 00:21:43,220
Isn't there some way I can persuade Mom?

402
00:21:43,423 --> 00:21:45,571
Moving another person's heart...

403
00:21:45,758 --> 00:21:48,058
is always the hardest thing to do.

404
00:21:48,290 --> 00:21:50,424
Look beyond the voice
that says she doesn't want to search,

405
00:21:50,633 --> 00:21:54,133
and find
the true feelings hidden underneath.

406
00:21:54,951 --> 00:21:56,771
Her true hidden feelings?

407
00:21:59,484 --> 00:22:01,451
(Kangsu Construction)

408
00:22:03,312 --> 00:22:05,464
I think this needs
a little more monitoring.

409
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:08,480
That's what I thought too,
but this part...

410
00:22:11,884 --> 00:22:12,957
Come on.

411
00:22:14,028 --> 00:22:15,228
That's not fair.

412
00:22:24,164 --> 00:22:27,597
Mr. Han, please send me the current status
of the second Joy upgrade.

413
00:22:27,833 --> 00:22:31,533
Pardon? I emailed it to you
about an hour ago.

414
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:33,150
Did you?

415
00:22:37,956 --> 00:22:39,536
I checked it already. Sorry.

416
00:22:42,333 --> 00:22:43,333
Manager Seo.

417
00:22:44,421 --> 00:22:47,225
Do you still have the second set
of drawings Lucas sent last week?

418
00:22:47,225 --> 00:22:48,225
Sorry?

419
00:22:48,225 --> 00:22:50,648
Bring them to my office.
I'll need them for the afternoon meeting.

420
00:22:51,599 --> 00:22:52,599
Okay.

421
00:23:01,999 --> 00:23:03,899
What's gotten into her today?

422
00:23:04,533 --> 00:23:06,597
She handed me
the wrong documents earlier too.

423
00:23:07,307 --> 00:23:08,307
You're right.

424
00:23:08,596 --> 00:23:10,920
I think something must be going on today.

425
00:23:15,024 --> 00:23:16,547
This is driving me crazy.

426
00:23:16,871 --> 00:23:18,523
Seriously, I swear...

427
00:23:18,973 --> 00:23:19,973
Honestly.

428
00:23:20,728 --> 00:23:21,928
What's wrong?

429
00:23:23,084 --> 00:23:24,771
What's wrong? You're asking what's wrong?

430
00:23:26,707 --> 00:23:30,007
Did anyone come into this office today?

431
00:23:31,088 --> 00:23:32,555
No, no one did.

432
00:23:34,119 --> 00:23:36,691
Then why is my desk like this?

433
00:23:37,372 --> 00:23:40,639
No one came in here,
so why is this office in such a mess?

434
00:23:41,724 --> 00:23:43,688
Well, just now, you...

435
00:23:44,028 --> 00:23:45,028
What?

436
00:23:45,469 --> 00:23:48,232
Are you saying I did this to my own desk?

437
00:23:48,951 --> 00:23:50,360
You're my assistant.

438
00:23:50,360 --> 00:23:52,925
You don't even know who's been
coming in and out of the CEO's office,

439
00:23:53,100 --> 00:23:54,648
and now you're trying
to pin the blame on me?

440
00:23:55,088 --> 00:23:57,800
This is an insult to the CEO
and a dereliction of duty!

441
00:23:59,419 --> 00:24:02,233
I'll go check the security cameras
right now.

442
00:24:02,675 --> 00:24:04,175
I'll find out
who came into this office today.

443
00:24:04,554 --> 00:24:07,091
What? Security cameras?

444
00:24:07,866 --> 00:24:08,933
I'll be back.

445
00:24:08,933 --> 00:24:09,933
Wait right there.

446
00:24:12,382 --> 00:24:14,957
If there's some internal problem,

447
00:24:14,957 --> 00:24:17,109
I don't want it becoming public knowledge.

448
00:24:17,109 --> 00:24:19,000
Don't check the cameras.

449
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:20,000
Ko Dae Chi!

450
00:24:23,299 --> 00:24:25,599
Just tell me. What on earth is going on?

451
00:24:26,036 --> 00:24:27,659
What?

452
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:31,800
Lately, it feels like you want me
to resign and leave on my own.

453
00:24:32,187 --> 00:24:33,700
Tell me why.

454
00:24:34,485 --> 00:24:36,352
And if it's a good reason, I'll resign.

455
00:24:36,803 --> 00:24:39,059
You'll resign?

456
00:24:40,281 --> 00:24:41,477
- Really?
- But only...

457
00:24:42,769 --> 00:24:44,269
if the reason is justified.

458
00:24:45,558 --> 00:24:48,744
Well, I've got plenty of reasons.

459
00:24:48,744 --> 00:24:51,064
I just can't say them right now.
I'll organize everything first,

460
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:52,233
then tell you all at once.

461
00:24:52,733 --> 00:24:53,733
For now, get out.

462
00:25:03,085 --> 00:25:04,085
How scary.

463
00:25:05,374 --> 00:25:08,741
No, it's fine. I've got more than enough
justifiable reasons, right?

464
00:25:11,085 --> 00:25:12,085
I don't.

465
00:25:12,683 --> 00:25:14,133
Well, if I don't have one, I can make one.

466
00:25:14,133 --> 00:25:16,579
Okay, bad mood.

467
00:25:16,579 --> 00:25:18,435
Low self-esteem. Poor attitude.

468
00:25:20,656 --> 00:25:21,656
I'm stuck.

469
00:25:27,064 --> 00:25:28,264
CEO Ko's acting up again?

470
00:25:32,485 --> 00:25:34,233
Yesterday he and his wife...

471
00:25:34,233 --> 00:25:36,633
showed up at our house
out of nowhere with beef.

472
00:25:37,525 --> 00:25:39,425
And today,
he's trying to pressure me into resigning.

473
00:25:40,517 --> 00:25:43,850
I'm reaching the limit of my patience.

474
00:25:44,837 --> 00:25:48,737
What could it be?
The one he wants gone is probably me.

475
00:25:53,763 --> 00:25:56,181
Yes. The lobby café?

476
00:25:57,363 --> 00:25:58,563
Okay. I'll be right down.

477
00:26:00,803 --> 00:26:03,100
I've got a guest. Good work.

478
00:26:04,683 --> 00:26:06,051
Okay. See you later.

479
00:26:09,667 --> 00:26:12,864
I'm in the lobby. Come down.

480
00:26:18,096 --> 00:26:19,096
Honey!

481
00:26:22,220 --> 00:26:23,920
What could be keeping him so busy?

482
00:26:34,175 --> 00:26:35,331
Excuse me.

483
00:26:38,133 --> 00:26:39,733
Are you perhaps the Chief Assistant
of Kangsu Group?

484
00:26:40,300 --> 00:26:42,280
Yes. I'm Seo Gwon Sik.

485
00:26:56,772 --> 00:26:59,523
Well, look who it is.

486
00:27:01,481 --> 00:27:02,481
Weren't we roommates?

487
00:27:04,055 --> 00:27:05,055
Sorry?

488
00:27:06,707 --> 00:27:09,805
What's wrong with him? Who is that guy?

489
00:27:12,984 --> 00:27:13,984
Mom.

490
00:27:19,041 --> 00:27:20,874
I think you've got the wrong idea.

491
00:27:21,645 --> 00:27:23,412
I don't believe we've met.

492
00:27:24,800 --> 00:27:27,421
What are you talking about?
You don't recognize me?

493
00:27:28,675 --> 00:27:31,509
It's me, Jeong Dong Pal.

494
00:27:34,075 --> 00:27:35,661
Dong Pal.

495
00:27:38,471 --> 00:27:40,871
We shared a room together
for five years...

496
00:27:42,461 --> 00:27:43,661
You've mistaken me for someone else.

497
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:10,800
(Our Happy Days)

498
00:28:11,005 --> 00:28:12,560
I'll get straight to the point.

499
00:28:12,560 --> 00:28:14,163
Break up with Gyeol immediately.

500
00:28:14,163 --> 00:28:15,004
Mother.

501
00:28:15,004 --> 00:28:16,717
Who are you calling "Mother?"

502
00:28:16,997 --> 00:28:18,368
You actually came all the way here,

503
00:28:18,368 --> 00:28:20,248
and you're leaving without seeing Bit Na?

504
00:28:20,248 --> 00:28:23,425
Once I've paid off
at least some of my debts, I'll come back.

505
00:28:23,425 --> 00:28:24,539
By then, it'll be too late!

506
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:25,900
Mother...

507
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:28,033
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
